text: Hans-Jürgen Heinsch (4 July 1940 – 14 July 2022) was a German footballer. He competed in the 1964 Summer Olympics, where he won a bronze medal for playing with the East Germany national football team. He also managed F.C. Hansa Rostock. He was born in Lübeck, Germany.
